\chapter{Introduction}
\label{Introduction:introduction}\label{Introduction:welcome-to-stickerbot-9000-documentation}\label{Introduction::doc}
Congratulations on acquiring a Stickerbot 9000! This amazing tool will bring you dozens of minutes of fund raising joy! As with any wonder of the world the Stickerbot 9000 requires proper care and handling. This manual will help you do just that.


\chapter{Installation}
\label{Installation:installation}\label{Installation::doc}
The Stickerbot 9000 ships setup and ready to make you money! Just plug it in, boot it up and rake in the cash.

\emph{Warning - This product is not guaranteed to work in Las Vegas, Nevada. No warranty coverage is provided to this location.}


\section{Setup}
\label{Installation:setup}
Time to make some money! To setup the Stickerbot 9000 just follow these simple steps.
\begin{enumerate}
\item {} 
Remove lock and open case.

\item {} 
Extract power cord from right side of bill collector.

\item {} 
Plug cord into power.

\item {} 
Run power cord through slot on side of case.

\item {} 
Close case and replace lock.

\end{enumerate}


\section{Packing}
\label{Installation:packing}
Now that your pockets are stuffed beyond capacity with cash, it is time to put away the Stickerbot 9000 and go party, or head home and distribute the money in a responsible manner. Whatever works for you.
\begin{enumerate}
\item {} 
Remove lock and open case.

\item {} 
Unplug power cord.

\item {} 
Remove cord from slot on side of case.

\item {} 
Coil cord into case to right of bill collector.

\item {} 
Close case and replace lock.

\end{enumerate}


\chapter{Power}
\label{Power::doc}\label{Power:power}

\section{Power On}
\label{Power:power-on}\begin{enumerate}
\item {} 
Remove lock and open case.

\item {} 
Switch power strip on.

\item {} 
Power on printer.
\begin{enumerate}
\item {} 
Remove wiring harness from between printer and bill collector.

\item {} 
Slide printer backwards until power button on top of printer is visible.

\item {} 
Push the power button.

\item {} 
Verify the ``Status'' light is lit.

\item {} 
Slide printer forwards into position. Verify printer engages sticker dispenser ramp.

\item {} 
Replace wiring harness between printer and bill collector.

\end{enumerate}

\item {} 
Power on EL lighting.
\begin{enumerate}
\item {} 
Push button on inverter installed just behind power strip.

\item {} 
Each press cycles through to a different mode.
\begin{enumerate}
\item {} 
Solid on.

\item {} 
Slow flash.

\item {} 
Fast flash.

\item {} 
Off

\end{enumerate}

\end{enumerate}

\item {} 
Close case and replace lock.

\end{enumerate}


\section{Power Off}
\label{Power:power-off}\begin{enumerate}
\item {} 
Remove lock and open case.

\item {} 
Turn off switch on power strip.

\item {} 
Close case and replace lock.

\end{enumerate}


\chapter{Servicing}
\label{Servicing::doc}\label{Servicing:servicing}
You didn't think Stickerbot 9000 would make you rich without any work did you? Luckily you don't have to do much.


\section{Replacing Sticker Roll}
\label{Servicing:replacing-sticker-roll}\begin{enumerate}
\item {} 
Remove lock and open case.

\item {} 
Remove wiring harness from between printer and bill collector.

\item {} 
Slide printer backwards until top of printer is visible.

\item {} 
Open top of printer and replace sticker roll.

\item {} 
Close top of printer.

\item {} 
Verify the ``Status'' light is lit. Press power button if light is not lit.

\item {} 
Slide printer forwards into position. Verify printer engages sticker dispenser ramp.

\item {} 
Replace wiring harness between printer and bill collector.

\item {} 
Close case and replace lock.

\end{enumerate}


\section{Collecting Your Cash}
\label{Servicing:collecting-your-cash}\begin{enumerate}
\item {} 
Remove lock and open case.

\item {} 
Remove wiring harness from between printer and bill collector.

\item {} 
Remove bill collector by rotating bottom toward you until feed clears case.

\item {} 
Slide release on bottom of bill hopper toward rear to unlock.

\item {} 
Slide bill hopper toward top of unit to remove.

\item {} 
Access door on side of bill hopper to remove money.

\item {} 
Replace bill hopper and slide down to lock.

\item {} 
Replace bill collector by sliding forward into place in case.

\item {} 
Replace wiring harness between printer and bill collector.

\item {} 
Close case and replace lock.

\end{enumerate}
